<br>
Page 1 = 8 Standard Spells I have loaded for movement (running around dangerous zones). <br>
<br>
Page 2 = The 8 most common spells I swap out when I get into a grind situation.<br>
<br>
Page 3-4 = Raid Situational Spells and the spells that didn't fit on page 2.<br>
<br>
Page 5-6 = Misc Spells that are used on occasion but have not moved to the back of the book.<br>
<br>
Page 7-8 = All enchant type spells, metals, clay, bars etc..<br>
<br>
Page 9-11 = All Illusion Spells<br>
<br>
Everything else is in the back of the book.<br>
<br>
Different players have different play styles, but I suggest putting the ones you swap out in a hurry all together on page 1 or 2. <br>
<br>
PS. The druid book you posted is horrible.  Why would you ever need Skin Like Wood, Skin Like Rock, or Skin Like Steel if you have Skin Like Diamond?.  Always move the obsolete spells to the back of the book so they are out of the way.  Or with the recent patch, you can now just delete them.  Although I won't be deleting any spells till I run out of room.  I still pull out 'back of the book spells' on occasion. <p>--<a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=134141">Tanzia</a><br>
