<br>
I put my most common 1-8 spell lineup on page 1&amp;2 running across rows.  I put my most common swap outs below them, so the swap out spell is in the same position as the main spell it replaces, but on the bottom.  <br>
<br>
Page 3/4 is alternate battle spells, invis, gate<br>
<br>
Page 5/6 is buffs, all my buffs in the top rows, other buffs in 3rd row.  Speed and clarity always at the start of the rows.<br>
<br>
Page 7/8 Utility spells, not commonly used (Identify, true north), lower damage nukes for when needed<br>
<br>
Page 9/10 Enchants<br>
<br>
Page 11/12 Visious Mana &amp; kind<br>
<br>
Page 13/14 Illusions - common<br>
Page 15/16 Illusions, other<br>
<br>
Page 17 on - old unused spells<br>
<br>
I have Hot Key slot 0 set up to call each page, so to main combat spells, i just need &lt;shift&gt; 0, 1..to flip thru the book i just need to press 1, 2, 3, 4 while on &lt;shift&gt; 0 hotkey tabs.  Then &lt;shift&gt; 1 to return to ready.  <br>
<br>
Always replace spells with the upgrade in the same slot, so you always know where your main dd spell is, from level 1 on.  Then it's all habit.<br>
